==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tailstock
<hw>Tail"stock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The sliding block
or support, in a lathe, which carries the dead spindle, or adjustable
center. The <contr>headstock</contr> supports the live
spindle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tail-water</ent>⟦br⟧
